<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> "Mostly in this book I shall specialize upon indications that there exists a transportory force that I shall call Teleportation." in <a href="http://www.sacred-texts.com/fort/lo/lo02.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sacred-texts.com/fort/lo/lo02.htm" rel="nofollow">Fort. C. <i>Lo!</i> at Sacred Texts.com), retrieved 4 January 2009)</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> "less well-known is the fact that Charles Fort coined the word in 1931" in Rickard, B. and Michell, J. <i>Unexplained Phenomena: a Rough Guide special</i> (Rough Guides, 2000 (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1858285895" class="internal">ISBN 1-85828-589-5</a>), p.3)</li>
<li id="cite_note-CommonGround-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-CommonGround_7-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.commonground.ca/iss/0410159/cg159_geoffUniv.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.commonground.ca/iss/0410159/cg159_geoffUniv.shtml" rel="nofollow">Common Ground</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Scientific_Exploration-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Exploration_8-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.scientificexploration.org/jse/articles/pdf/16.3_corliss.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.scientificexploration.org/jse/articles/pdf/16.3_corliss.pdf" rel="nofollow">Scientific Exploration</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Magonia-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Magonia_9-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.magonia.demon.co.uk/arc/80/confessions.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.magonia.demon.co.uk/arc/80/confessions.htm" rel="nofollow">Confessions</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.war-ofthe-worlds.co.uk/searchers.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.war-ofthe-worlds.co.uk/searchers.htm" rel="nofollow">War of the Worlds site profile</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
